&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABOUT THE OPPORTUNITY&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an &lt;strong&gt;Events &amp;amp; Experiences Intern &lt;/strong&gt;to join the KHAITE team for this Fall &#39;26 Semester. This role will report to the &lt;strong&gt;Global&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;Director, Events &amp;amp; Experiences &lt;/strong&gt;and will be based out of the NYC HQ offices. This internship is unpaid and for college credit only.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ESSENTIAL DUTIES &amp;amp; RESPONSIBILITIES&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in the coordination and execution of all KHAITE Events, including Show Styling, Show, Market, VIC Events, Cocktails, Dinners, and Retail Activations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with vendor research/outreach in local and new markets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help create Event Overview Decks, Recap Reports, and Production Schedules.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Logistical support in messengering, shipping, deliveries, and pick-ups of event materials.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support in maintaining and upkeeping local inventory and supplies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Expense organization and management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working on-site during local New York based events.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide general administrative support as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
