&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interpersonal Skills:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong organizational skills and ability to multitask in a fast-paced environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong written and verbal communication skills; with a strong attention to details.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Passion for luxury fashion, events, experiential marketing, and client relations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Keen interest for fashion and eagerness to immerse themselves in the industry.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Education/Experience:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Currently enrolled for a Bachelor’s Degree; preferably in Communications, Fashion, Marketing, Event Planning, or a related field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in MS Office Applications, including Outlook, Excel, and PowerPoint as well as the Google Suite&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prior experience in event planning, PR, client relations, or styling is preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note: This job description does not list all the duties of the job. Employees may be asked by management to perform other duties. The employer has the right to revise this job description at any time.&lt;/p&gt;
